RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 81. Claiming Purse 34400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUSKOKA SUMMER was allowed to settle trailing the pack down the backside, saved ground seeing the field around the turn, swung out widest in the seven path gaining momentum at the top of the lane and wore down the leaders through the entire stretch to just hold in a tight photo for the win. SWIRLING DANCER pressed the pace inside down the back straight, offered only mild pressure on the fence throughout the turn, never gave in down the stretch, determinedly surged inside at the furlong pole and just missed timing the nod at the wire for the win. BIG GINGER had a slim advantage outside down the backstretch, opened up slightly on the chasing rival to her inside through the turn, stubbornly fought on down the stretch clinging to the lead and gave way grudgingly with runners on each side in the final few jumps before the wire to hold for third money. VERY SAVVY had one foe beaten down the backside, made little headway outside of horses through the turn, angled out to be in the six path in upper stretch and finished up mildly to the wire to settle on the fringes. TAYLORMOON stalked near the rear on the inside down the back straight, rallied smartly on the fence at the quarter pole, shifted out to the three path to pose a threat at the top of the lane, could not sustain the run and stalled at the sixteenth pole. MOONBRIGHT travelled just behind the front pair inside of rivals down the backstretch, was roused at the quarter pole keeping pace with the leaders, shifted out to be four wide in the mix between horses straightening out for the drive but could not go on with others in the final furlong. PERFECT PROVISION settled on the outside in the second flight outside of runners down the backstretch, continued to chase the leaders outside around the bend, angled out to be in the five path with rivals on either side turning for home but could not find more late to get into contention in deep stretch.

SHEZ A SEALY lacked early speed trailing the field, came out nine to ten wide for the drive, was not a threat. RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 3 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 78. Claiming Purse 23700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MENDELJOHN (IRE) was content to sit alone tracking the pacesetter down the backstretch, edged a little closer to the frontrunner around the turn and wore down the leader under left handed encouragement in deep stretch to get up in the final jump. FANCY PHYLLIS took command from the onset, dictated the pace through the turn with little pressure from other rivals and ran on gamely clinging to the lead at the furlong marker but was caught in the final nod at the wire by the winner. MIDNIGHT MOONSHINE was in a good spot on the outside watching the top two down the backstretch, kept pace with the leaders travelling three wide through the turn and willingly finished down the stretch to capture third money. PASSTHEPUDDINPLEAZ had a good position tracking the front two on the rail down the backside, continued on the fence keeping pace with the leaders around the bend, lacked running room nestled behind the leader at the top of the lane and could not extend his stride fully to the wire never really having a clear path through the stretch. MIA AND ME was coaxed on the rail to get interested down the backside, came under a hard ride midway on the turn but made little impression and was not a factor in the drive to the finish line. C R HOT SHOT was void of early speed trailing down the backstretch, offered a mild run picking up runners inside at the quarter pole but could not get into contention running to the wire. WILD CONVERSATION broke slowly on the start, had one rival beaten down the back straight, made no impact running around the turn and had little to show in the stretch drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 4 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 29700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 14 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DREAMING OF AUDREY broke on top then was allowed to settle racing off the leader in behind and between foes, stalked into the turn, moved four wide late on that bend, bid in mid-stretch, drifted out badly the remainder of the way under left-handed urging but edged away late. LOADED VIXEN quickly moved to the lead, set the pace racing off the rail, was mostly in the two to three path, challenged by a far-outside rival in mid-stretch, dug in and fought on but was outfinished. NORTHERN RUBY was unhurried in the early going, raced five wide early on the turn but moved out a bit for room, came into upper stretch seven deep, kept on well to gain show honors. TRIZZEL TRAZZEL was outsprinted in the early going, was off the fence through the turn in the three then four path, was in tight four deep at the top of the stretch between runners, navigated traffic splitting rivals then shifting in and gained belatedly to make the super. NO WHAMMIE raced up close in behind the leaders going two to three wide through the turn, ran on evenly. AIRY FAIRY was forwardly-placed between runners up the backstretch but exchanged hard bumps inside and out and checked sharply about the four- and one-half dropping back to the rear, swung nine wide turning for home, kicked on with mild and willing late interest. BODACIOUS MISS pursued the leader in close range three to four wide, weakened in the stretch. MI TORMENTA exchanged a bump at the start, settled between foes three wide on the turn, ran on evenly. HIT AND RUN exchanged a bump at the start, was encouraged forward, shifted in when in tight nearing the nine-sixteenths exchanged some contact and put others in tight quarters, saved ground on the turn, had no late impact. ENDORPHIN RUSH was off the early pace, advanced some five wide early on the turn, was in a bit tight between foes at the top of the stretch, flattened out. CHARLOTTE'S SILVER was forwardly-placed inside heading up the backstretch, exchanged some hard bumps and steadied at the four- and one-half, failed to rally thereafter.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HYPER AWAKENING was content on the inside keeping a close eye on the dueling leaders around the turn, began to reel the tiring early leaders three wide in upper stretch, seized control at the sixteenth pole and was drawing off when crossing the finish line. GOODNIGHTNGODBLESS was in a good position on the outside watching the engaging pair throughout the turn, started to close in on the tiring leaders four wide at the top of the stretch and offered a good finish besting the rest at the wire. SILENT PATSY was situated on the rail stalking in the third flight around the bend, was urged left handed shifted out to the four path in upper stretch, darted back inside at the eighth pole and surged late between runners to get up for third money in deep stretch. SISTER COUSIN prompted the pace down the backstretch on the outside, collared the leader at the quarter pole, took control briefly at the furlong marker but faltered in the final seventy yards to settle for a minor role in the end. LADIES RUM was outside her rival stalking the leaders in the third flight in the turn, angled outside five wide turning for home and was gaining steadily in the stretch closing the gap on the leaders. I'M AWESOME stalked near the rear down the backstretch, started a mild run passing foes three wide at the quarter pole, shifted outside in the five path at the top of the lane and finished up mildly to the wire. EMPTY CHAIRS set the pace under a hold while hounded outside down the backstretch, was headed outside at the quarter pole, gave way to runners in upper stretch and shortened stride stopping quickly in the final sixteenth. BRAZILIAN LEGACY hesitated slightly at the start, co-trailed between runners at the half, made a mild run on the fence in the turn but could not get involved in the drive to the wire. SILVER LASSO hopped on the start, co-trailed on the inside with the other rivals that were off poorly on the break, could not quicken with others through the turn and was not a presence in the stretch drive. BLING D'MONEY HOME had a poor start to begin, trailed the field shifting off the fence down the back straight, offered little run three wide outside horses around the turn and lacked a rally down the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILDFIRE travelled four wide outside horses in midfield galloping along under a tight hold down the backstretch, took closer order tracking the top pair outside into the turn, turned up the pressure bidding for the lead three wide at the quarter pole, took over control by the sixteenth pole and was clearing off when crossing the line for the score. ANOTHER PINKY was under a snug rein improving on the fence down the backside to force the pace inside by the half, began to inch away up top midway through the turn, braced for the challenge by the winner outside at the top of the lane but was no match for the winner in deep stretch. TAPPING A RHYTHM bobbled on the start, crept closer with runners on either side at the quarter pole, swung outside of rivals four wide turning for home and closed in to capture the show award in the end. PORT RENFREW was allowed to settle trailing the compact field down the backstretch, rallied three wide around horses at the three eighths marker, angled out to the four path for the stretch drive and won the duel for the minors through the lane. TACHYON SPEED had one rival beaten while stalking on the fence down the backside, saved ground seeing the field throughout the turn and passed tired runners in the drive to the finish line. CRIMSON NIGHTS prompted the pace in the two path in the early going, was then throttled down to watch the front trio up front around the bend, had a chance on the rail in upper stretch for a small piece of the prize but could not find more late and levelled off in the last sixteenth. WORK IT BABY had a narrow advantage setting a modest tempo up front down the backside, was relegated to a chasing role between horses on the turn, could not quicken with the leaders on either side at the quarter pole and backed away through the field in the final furlong.
